WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.460 --> 00:00:04.128
The chief supply chain officer, or CSCO,

2
00:00:04.128 --> 00:00:07.448
exercises knowledge of agency program planning,

3
00:00:07.448 --> 00:00:10.659
funding, and management information systems.

4
00:00:10.659 --> 00:00:14.000
The CSCO utilizes broad knowledge and skills

5
00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:16.313
of organization functions and activities

6
00:00:16.313 --> 00:00:18.244
to provide logistical support,

7
00:00:18.244 --> 00:00:20.438
while coordinating and evaluating the efforts

8
00:00:20.438 --> 00:00:24.350
of functional specialists to identify specific requirements

9
00:00:24.350 --> 00:00:26.729
to develop and adjust plans and schedules

10
00:00:26.729 --> 00:00:29.111
for the actions needed to meet requirements

11
00:00:29.111 --> 00:00:30.721
in a timely manner.

12
00:00:30.721 --> 00:00:34.888
The CSCO plans, forecasts, and executes budget for supplies,

13
00:00:35.982 --> 00:00:40.160
subsistence, durable medical equipment, medical gases,

14
00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:43.320
expendable and non-expendable and capital equipment,

15
00:00:43.320 --> 00:00:46.551
inventory management, warehouse operations,

16
00:00:46.551 --> 00:00:48.667
transportation, and distribution.

